Figure 8. Hemodynamic and catecholamine responses to mental challenge (playing a video game) in healthy humans There are increases in heart rate (HR), blood pressure (BP), and forearm blood flow (FBF) and concurrent increases in total body and forearm norepinephrine spillover (TB NE SO and FA NE SO), yet arterial and arm venous concentrations of epinephrine ([EPI]) remain unchanged. This pattern exemplifies active attention without distress.
Compr Physiol. Author manuscript; available in PMC 2017 January 30.

