Figure 10. Estimates of rates of norepinephrine synthesis, vesicular recycling, release, neuronal and extraneuronal uptake, and metabolism in cardiac sympathetic nerves in healthy humans and patients with congestive heart failure Note that under resting conditions most of the turnover of norepinephrine is from net vesicular leakage, not release escaping reuptake. Cardiac norepinephrine spillover is influenced by both exocytotic release and neuronal reuptake.
Compr Physiol. Author manuscript; available in PMC 2017 January 30.

