Figure 16. Adrenaline and ACTH responses to different stressors in humans, from a metaanalysis of the literature There is excellent agreement between adrenomedullary and adrenocortical activation. For instance, exposure to cold exerts little or no adrenomedullary or adrenocortical activation, whereas insulin-induced hypoglycemia evokes large-magnitude adrenomedullary and adrenocortical activation.
Compr Physiol. Author manuscript; available in PMC 2017 January 30.

